jfxtras.labs.scene.control.window

Class WindowIcon

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.Parent
        • javafx.scene.layout.Region

            • jfxtras.labs.scene.control.window.WindowIcon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, javafx.scene.control.Skinnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CloseIcon, MinimizeIcon, RotateIcon

    public class WindowIcon
extends javafx.scene.control.Control
    A window icon that is the visual representation of an action that can be performed on the window. Usually, icons are shown in the titlebar of a window and react on clicking gestures.
